</style><div class="docx-wrapper"><section class="docx" style="padding: 70.85pt 70.85pt 56.7pt; width: 595pt; min-height: 842pt;"><article><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold; min-height: 24pt; font-size: 24pt;">The By-laws of the </span><span style="font-weight: bold; min-height: 24pt; font-size: 24pt;">RedCom</span><span style="font-weight: bold; min-height: 24pt; font-size: 24pt;"> League</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Number of teams</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>12</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Divisions </span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>3 (</span><span>Random assignment</span><span>)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>After each season, the divisions will be recast randomly</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Fee:</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>50$ per Season/Team</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Seasons 2022 and 2023 (i.e. 100 $) to be paid upfront before Startup Draft </span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>League fees will be managed through </span><span>Leaguesafe</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Future Draft Picks can be traded only in case that Participation fee for that season has been paid in full</span><span>.</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through; color: rgb(192, 0, 0);">Late payment for 2024 will cause Rookie Picks to be removed from the involved manager (more details will follow)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">New rule applicable from 2023-03-25 onwards:</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">League fees must be paid </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">1</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> year in advance</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">. Deadline: </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">1 day</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">prior to</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> the official NFL rookie draft </span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">Example</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> 1)</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> in order to have no penalty rookie picks removed, league fee 2025 must be paid until approx. end April 2024</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">Example 2) </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">in order to have no penalty rookie picks removed, league fee 2026 must be paid until approx. end April 2025 </span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">and so on…</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">In case of delayed </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">payments,</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> the following penalty will be applied</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">Up to 1 week delay = </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">no</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> 1</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>st</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> round draft pick in the corresponding draft year </span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">(i.e. 2025 in example 1, 2026 in example 2)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">Up to 2 weeks delay = no 1</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>st</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> + 2</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>nd</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> round draft pick</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">Up to 3 weeks delay = no 1</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>st</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> + 2</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>nd</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> + 3</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>rd</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> round draft pick</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">Up to 4 weeks delay = no 1</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>st</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> + 2</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>nd</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> + 3</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>rd</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>  </sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);">+  4</span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"><sup>th</sup></span><span style="color: rgb(83, 129, 53);"> round draft pick</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Yearly Prizes:</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1st Place = 350 $</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2nd Place = 175 $</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>3rd Place = 75 $</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Starting Lineup:</span><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">10 Roster Spots</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 QB</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2 RB</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2 WR</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 TE</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 Super Flex</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 Flex</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 K</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-1-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 DEF</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Super Flex = QB, RB, WR or TE</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Flex = RB, WR or TE</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Each Starting Lineup slot will lock individually at the scheduled game time of the player in each slot.</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Positional Limits</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>A max. </span><span>of </span><span>2 DEF can be held on Roster</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Startup Draft Positions:</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Drawn at random when league is paid in full</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Startup Draft:</span><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span>24 round serpentine (snake) online draft - Veterans &amp; Free agents only</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Online Slow Draft with a </span><span>12-hour</span><span> timer per pick</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Rookie Draft 2022:</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Reversed order of Startup Draft / 4 Rounds in Snake format</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Online Slow Draft with a </span><span>12-hour</span><span> timer per pick</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Rookie Draft 2023 and onwards</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Linear Drafts of 4 rounds, will include rookies only and will take place after the NFL draft</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Online Slow Draft with </span><span>an</span><span> </span><span>8 </span><span>hour</span><span>s</span><span> timer per pick</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Draft Picks Assignment</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-2-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Will be assigned based on Max Points For (during Regular Season) for the 9 teams not winning any Prizes </span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>(i.e. Team with lowest Max PF will get 1st Pick of each Round, Team with 2nd lowest Max PF will get 2nd Pick, etc.)</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-2-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>10th Pick of each Round will be assigned to 3rd Placed Team of previous Season</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-2-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>11th Pick of each Round will be assigned to 2nd Placed Team of previous Season</span></p><p class="docx_listenabsatz docx-num-2-0" style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>12th Pick of each Round will be assigned to 1st Placed Team of previous Season</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Format (Regular Season):</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Weeks 1-14</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Head 2 Head Matchups (two games each against Divisional Teams / one game each against </span><span>non Divisional</span><span> Teams)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Format (League Playoffs):</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Six (6) teams advance to League Playoffs.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Three (3) Division winners&nbsp;- Seeds #1 - #3 based on best Record / Tie breaker is Points For</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Two (2) teams with the best records among the remaining teams - Seeds #4 - #5 based on best Record / Tie breaker is Points For</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>One (1) team with the highest scored points for among the remaining teams - Seed #6</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Weeks 15-17</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Top 2 seeds get bye week in Week 15</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>During Week 15, seed #3 plays against seed #6 / seed #4 plays against seed #5. The winners move on to the next round</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>During Weeks 16, seeds #1 will play against the lowest remaining seeded team and seed #2, will play against the highest remaining from Wild Card Round&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>During Week 17, there will be the </span><span>RedCom</span><span> Bowl and the final for 3rd Place</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Free Agency In Season:</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Waivers by way of blind bidding (FAAB)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Each team gets $100 blind bidding “dollars” for the entire Season</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Continuous Waivers 12am EST</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 weekly free agency (FA) on Sunday</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>NFL players whose teams played on Thursday may be dropped from rosters on Friday as long as they were not in that team’s Thursday’s starting lineup</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">TIME PLAYERS ARE ON WAIVERS AFTER DROP</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1 Day</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">GAMES WAIVERS CLEAR</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Tuesday End of Day (00:00 PST)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Free Agency Off Season:</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>First free agency is scheduled one day after Rookie draft is completed</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Each team gets $100 blind bidding “dollars” for the entire Off-season</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Continuous Waivers 12am EST for the entire Off-Season</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">TIME TO REVIEW PENDING TRADES</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>None - Trades are processed immediately</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Any sign of collusion to maximize the chance of winning will be examined </span><span>throughfully</span><span> and in confirmed cases will cause the removal of the involved managers from the League.</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Trade Deadline</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>None</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Roster Requirement</span><span>:</span><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>24 Total roster spots during NFL season</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>4 Taxi Squad slots</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>5 Injured Reserve (IR) slots / Eligible IR player status types are SUS (suspended) / COV (covid) &amp; IR (Injured reserve)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Players with (Q) Questionable,  (D) Doubtful or (O) Out designation are not eligible for the injured reserve</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Scoring</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Passing Yards= +0.04 per yard </span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> </span><span>(25 yards = 1 point)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Passing TD = +4</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2-Pt Conversion = +2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Pass Intercepted= -2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Rushing Yards = +0.1 per yard</span><span> (</span><span>(10 yards = 1 point)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Rushing TD = +6</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2-Pt Conversion = +2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Reception = +0.50</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Receiving Yards = +0.1 per yard </span><span> </span><span>(10 yards = 1 point)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Receiving TD = +6</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2-Pt Conversion = +</span><span>2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points per Field Goal Yard = +0.05</span><span> </span><span>(e.g. 50 yds FG = 2.5 Pts)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>PAT Made = +0.5</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Defense TD = +6</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points Allowed 0 = +10</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points Allowed 1-6 = +7</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points Allowed 7-13 = +4</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points Allowed 14-20 = +1</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points Allowed 28-34 = -1</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Points Allowed 35+ = -4</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Sacks = +1</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Interceptions = +2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Fumble Recovery = +2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Safety = +2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Blocked Kick = +1</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Special Teams TD = +6</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Special Teams Fumble Recovery = +2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Miscellaneous</span><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span>Fumble Lost = -2</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>Fumble Recovery TD = +6</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Tie Breaker</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>I</span><span>n case of a tie during the playoffs the following tie-breaker rules will apply:</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>1) Bench Points Total (not including Taxi and IR)</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>2) QB Points</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>3) RB Points</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>4) WR Points</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Rule changes</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span class="docx-tab-stop"> </span></span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>All formal rule changes must be done during the offseason. The offseason period is considered the day after the </span><span>RedCom</span><span> Superbowl and the day before the rookie draft occurs. </span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"><span>To amend any rule or regulation as defined in the bylaws, or to add another rule or regulation to it, a league member must bring the suggestion to the attention of the Commissioner in writing. The Commissioner will then present all of the specifics of the rules to the league members. A vote will be held </span><span style="color: rgb(0, 176, 80);">and</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 176, 80);"> 75 % members of the league (9 of 12) must vote in </span><span style="color: rgb(0, 176, 80);">favour</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 176, 80);"> </span><span style="text-decoration: line-through; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">all members of the league must vote unanimously</span><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);"> </span><span>to change an existing rule or add a new rule. If a suggestion is voted down, the owner who offered the suggestion can revise the rule offering and present again. If the suggestion is voted down a second time, the matter will be closed for that season and can be reopened the following offseason.</span></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p><p style="margin-left: 35.45pt;"></p></article></section></div>
